  "notes": "Primary source: RFEG club microsite (federative code MM23, recorrido 'EL VALLE', selector value 2305), which lists per-hole meters, par, handicap, and Vc/Vs for all four tees for both genders. Distances, pars, and totals cross-check exactly with the official GNK Golf printed scorecard PDF (2019). Discrepancies: (1) Stroke index — RFEG assigns one allocation to Blancas/Amarillas (used here, per men's championship tee) and a different one to Azules/Rojas (1:9, 2:5, 3:1, 4:15, 5:7, 6:17, 7:3, 8:13, 9:11, 10:12, 11:18, 12:14, 13:4, 14:10, 15:16, 16:2, 17:8, 18:6); the 2019 GNK printed card shows an older single allocation (1:8, 2:2, 3:5, 4:16, 5:10, 6:13, 7:6, 8:7, 9:9, 10:17, 11:18, 12:11, 13:1, 14:14, 15:15, 16:3, 17:12, 18:4). RFEG current data was preferred. (2) Ratings on the 2019 printed card (e.g. Blancas M 73.6) differ slightly from current RFEG ratings (73.3/135); RFEG used. RFEG per-nine ratings, men — Blancas: ida 37.7/132, vuelta 35.6/139; Amarillas: 35.5/129, 34.0/131; Azules: 34.8/128, 33.2/130; Rojas: 32.7/102, 31.3/112. Women — Blancas: 41.8/145, 38.9/136; Amarillas: 39.3/138, 37.5/139; Azules: 38.6/136, 36.6/138; Rojas: 35.3/126, 33.7/121. Internal consistency verified: pars sum 36+35=71, SI is a permutation of 1-18, each tee's 18 distances sum exactly to its total."
